Attackers use the Nmap tool to perform ARP ping scan for discovering live hosts in the network. 
In Zenmap, the -PR option is used to perform ARP ping scan.

-sn is the Nmap command to disable the port scan.
Since Nmap uses ARP ping scan as the default ping scan, to disable it and perform other desired ping scans.

syntax:- nmap -PT <ip address>
command:- nmap -sn -PR 192.168.187.208
